commits.message:
Refactor email link sign-in and update configurations

This commit refactors the email link sign-in process for both Android and iOS platforms.

Key changes include:
- Updated Firebase Hosting `apple-app-site-association` paths from `/tyche/signin` to `/sign-in/*`.
- Modified Android Manifest intent filter path prefix for sign-in from `/signin` to `/sign-in`.
- Introduced `IosBundleIdProvider` in Android core and its implementation `LocalIosBundleIdProvider` to provide the iOS bundle ID. This is now used in `AuthenticationFirebaseDataSource` for setting Android package name and iOS bundle ID in `ActionCodeSettings`.
- Added `AndroidPackageNameProvider` in iOS Core and its implementation `LocalAndroidPackageNameProvider` to provide the Android package name. This is used in `AuthenticationFirebaseDataSource` for `ActionCodeSettings`.
- Updated `signInLinkUrlTemplate` in `gradle.properties` and `AppConfig.xcconfig` to use `/sign-in/` path.
- Added `iosBundleId` to `gradle.properties` and `ANDROID_PACKAGE_NAME` to `AppConfig.xcconfig`.
- Moved `emailLinkSignInView` composable content from `EmailLinkSignInViewProvider.kt` (deleted) to `SignInWithEmailLinkNavViewProvider.kt` and updated deep link URI pattern.
- Updated string resources for account verification description.
- Removed an unnecessary `println` statement in `RetrofitExceptionHandler.kt`.
- Added `AppDelegate.swift` in the iOS project to configure FirebaseApp.
- Updated project files to include new provider files and `AppDelegate.swift`.

pull_request.title: Add status subresource to StorageProfile
pull_request.body:
We have been observing flaky failures in the StorageProfile functional tests.

The root cause appears to be a race condition. Each test resets the spec upon completion, but the controller is likely still processing the previous state when the next test begins. Without a status field, the test has no way to confirm that the controller has finished reconciling the previous state.

This change introduces a status subresource to the StorageProfile. This allows tests and clients to observe the resource's actual state and wait for the status field to be populated - signaling that reconciliation is complete before proceeding.

The implementation includes:

1. Adding the +kubebuilder:subresource:status annotation to the StorageProfile type.
2. Updating the controller to handle status updates separately from the spec.
3. Regenerating the CRD to support the status subresource.

comment.body:
Regarding

> In order to enable this, we will provide the APK through an alternative distribution channel. Details on the exact method and platform are still under consideration ‚Äî we welcome your input.

and considering

> To be transparent: The SDK for the online issuance process (with the online picture verification step) is currently not open source. However, it is possible to have the e-ID issued on site ([see BGEID, Art. 17](https://www.fedlex.admin.ch/eli/fga/2025/20/de#art_17)). We will check with the relevant authorities whether the SDK can also be published.

I guess the [**Accrescent**](https://accrescent.app/) app store would be better suited as an alternative distribution channel for the Swiyu app.

Accrescent is open source, free to use and very straight-forward to implement/use for publishers, see their [developer guide](https://accrescent.app/docs/guide/getting-started/index.html). Unfortunately, it's currently [invite-only](https://accrescent.app/docs/guide/getting-started/new-app.html#creating-an-account), but that's supposed to change in the [not-so-distant future](https://blog.accrescent.app/posts/progress-update-and-roadmap). If interested, you could also apply to get allow-listed for the time being.

Accrescent is [directly available](https://accrescent.app/faq#verifying) from GrapheneOS' own (minimal) app store and will likely become way more relevant in the future ‚Äì given the project reaches its [funding goal of 5'800 $/month](https://blog.accrescent.app/posts/the-future-of-accrescent/#where-were-at)ü§û

pull_request.title: Add status subresource to StorageProfile
pull_request.body:
We have been observing flaky failures in the StorageProfile functional tests.

The root cause appears to be a race condition. Each test resets the spec upon completion, but the controller is likely still processing the previous state when the next test begins. Without a status field, the test has no way to confirm that the controller has finished reconciling the previous state.

This change introduces a status subresource to the StorageProfile. This allows tests and clients to observe the resource's actual state and wait for the status field to be populated - signaling that reconciliation is complete before proceeding.

The implementation includes:

1. Adding the +kubebuilder:subresource:status annotation to the StorageProfile type.
2. Updating the controller to handle status updates separately from the spec.
3. Regenerating the CRD to support the status subresource.

pull_request.title: chore(deps-dev): bump jest-environment-jsdom from 29.7.0 to 30.0.5
pull_request.body:
Bumps [jest-environment-jsdom](https://github.com/jestjs/jest/tree/HEAD/packages/jest-environment-jsdom) from 29.7.0 to 30.0.5.
Release notes

Sourced from jest-environment-jsdom's releases.

30.0.2

What's Changed

Fixes

  • [jest-matcher-utils] Make 'deepCyclicCopyObject' safer by setting descriptors to a null-prototype object (#15689)
  • [jest-util] Make garbage collection protection property writable (#15689)

Full Changelog: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md

Jest 30.0.1

What's Changed

Features

  • [jest-resolver] Implement the defaultAsyncResolver (#15679)

Fixes

  • [jest-resolver] Resolve builtin modules correctly (#15683)
  • [jest-environment-node, jest-util] Avoid setting globals cleanup protection symbol when feature is off (#15684)

Chore & Maintenance

  • [*] Remove and deprecate jest-repl package (#15673)
  • [jest-resolver] Replace custom isBuiltinModule with node's isBuiltin (#15685)

New Contributors

  • @‚Äãvovkasm made their first contribution in jestjs/jest#15687

Full Changelog: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md

Jest 30

Today we are happy to announce the release of Jest 30. This release features a substantial number of changes, fixes, and improvements. While it is one of the largest major releases of Jest ever, we admit that three years for a major release is too long. In the future, we are aiming to make more frequent major releases to keep Jest great for the next decade.

If you want to skip all the news and just get going, run npm install jest@^30.0.0 and follow the migration guide: Upgrading from Jest 29 to 30.

Read the full blog post

Features

  • [*] Renamed globalsCleanupMode to globalsCleanup and --waitNextEventLoopTurnForUnhandledRejectionEvents to --waitForUnhandledRejections
  • [expect] Add ArrayOf asymmetric matcher for validating array elements. (#15567)
  • [babel-jest] Add option excludeJestPreset to allow opting out of babel-preset-jest (#15164)
  • [expect] Revert #15038 to fix expect(fn).toHaveBeenCalledWith(expect.objectContaining(...)) when there are multiple calls (#15508)
  • [jest-circus, jest-cli, jest-config] Add waitNextEventLoopTurnForUnhandledRejectionEvents flag to minimise performance impact of correct detection of unhandled promise rejections introduced in #14315 (#14681)
  • [jest-circus] Add a waitBeforeRetry option to jest.retryTimes (#14738)
  • [jest-circus] Add a retryImmediately option to jest.retryTimes (#14696)
  • [jest-circus, jest-jasmine2] Allow setupFilesAfterEnv to export an async function (#10962)
  • [jest-circus, jest-test-result] Add startedAt timestamp in TestCaseResultObject within onTestCaseResult (#15145)

... (truncated)

Changelog

Sourced from jest-environment-jsdom's changelog.

30.0.5

Features

  • [jest-config] Allow testMatch to take a string value
  • [jest-worker] Let workerIdleMemoryLimit accept 0 to always restart worker child processes

Fixes

  • [expect] Fix bigint error (#15702)

30.0.4

Features

  • [expect] The Inverse type is now exported (#15714)
  • [expect] feat: support async functions in toBe (#15704)

Fixes

  • [jest] jest --onlyFailures --listTests now correctly lists only failed tests (#15700)
  • [jest-snapshot] Handle line endings in snapshots (#15708)

30.0.3

Fixes

  • [jest-config] Fix ESM TS config loading in a CJS project (#15694)

pull_request.body:
Bumps [lint-staged](https://github.com/lint-staged/lint-staged) from 15.5.0 to 16.1.5.
Release notes

Sourced from lint-staged's releases.

v16.1.5

Patch Changes

  • #1608 4e3ce22 Thanks @‚Äãsrsatt! - Detect the git repo's top-level directory correctly when in a worktree.

v16.1.4

Patch Changes

  • #1604 90b37b0 Thanks @‚Äãiiroj! - Add another types field to package.json to make even more sure NPM detects that lint-staged includes built-in TypeScript type definitions.

v16.1.3

Patch Changes

  • #1602 7ea700b Thanks @‚Äãdword-design! - Add the types field to package.json to make sure NPM detects lint-staged includes built-in TypeScript type definitions.

v16.1.2

Patch Changes

  • #1570 a7c0c88 Thanks @‚ÄãItsNickBarry! - When using --diff-filter with the D option to include deleted staged files, lint-staged no longer tries to stage the deleted files, unless they're no longer deleted. Previously this caused an error from git add like fatal: pathspec 'deleted-file' did not match any files.

  • 38f942e Thanks @‚Äãiiroj! - Removed an extraneous log entry that printed shouldHidePArtiallyStagedFiles to console output.

v16.1.1

Patch Changes

  • #1565 3686977 Thanks @‚Äãiiroj! - Lint-staged now explicitly warns about potential data loss when using --no-stash.

  • #1571 02299a9 Thanks @‚Äãiiroj! - Function tasks (introduced in v16.0.0) only receive the staged files matching the configured glob, instead of all staged files.

  • #1563 bc61c74 Thanks @‚Äãiiroj! - This version fixes incorrect behavior where unstaged changes were committed when using the --no-stash option. This happened because --no-stash implied --no-hide-partially-staged, meaning unstaged changes to files which also had other staged changes were added to the commit by lint-staged; this is no longer the case.

    The previous (incorrect) behavior can still be achieved by using both options --no-stash --no-hide-partially-staged at the same time.

v16.1.0

Minor Changes

  • #1536 e729daa Thanks @‚Äãiiroj! - A new flag --no-revert has been introduced for when task modifications should be applied to the index before aborting the commit in case of errors. By default, lint-staged will clear all task modifications and revert to the original state.

  • #1550 b27fa3f Thanks @‚Äãiiroj! - Lint-staged now ignores symlinks and leaves them out from the list of staged files.

issue.title: Impl√©mentation du module de d√©tection de maladies des plantes
issue.body:
## Description

Ce PR impl√©mente le module de d√©tection de maladies des plantes pour le syst√®me de surveillance agricole en Rust. Il s'agit du premier module du syst√®me qui servira de base pour les autres modules de pr√©diction.

### Fonctionnalit√©s impl√©ment√©es

- **Structure du projet** avec workspace Cargo
- **Module commun** pour les fonctionnalit√©s partag√©es entre tous les modules
- **Module de d√©tection de maladies** avec:
  - Mod√®le Random Forest pour les donn√©es de capteurs
  - Mod√®le CNN pour les images
  - Types et utilitaires pour la d√©tection de maladies
- **API web** avec endpoints pour la d√©tection de maladies
- **Documentation** et fichiers de configuration

### Architecture

Le projet est organis√© en un workspace Cargo avec plusieurs crates:
- **common**: Fonctionnalit√©s partag√©es entre tous les modules
- **disease_detection**: D√©tection de maladies des plantes
- **api**: API web pour acc√©der aux fonctionnalit√©s

### Technologies utilis√©es

- **Rust**: Langage de programmation principal
- **Cargo**: Gestionnaire de paquets et syst√®me de build
- **Actix-web**: Framework web pour l'API
- **Diesel**: ORM pour l'acc√®s √† la base de donn√©es PostgreSQL
- **tch-rs**: Bindings PyTorch pour les mod√®les CNN
- **linfa**: Framework de machine learning pour les mod√®les classiques

### Comment tester

1. Cloner le d√©p√¥t
2. Ex√©cuter le script d'initialisation: `./init.sh`
3. Lancer l'API: `cargo run -p api`
4. Tester les endpoints avec curl:

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/disease-detection/sensor \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "latitude": 48.8566,
    "longitude": 2.3522,
    "soil_moisture": 35.5,
    "air_humidity": 65.2,
    "temperature": 22.3,
    "soil_ph": 6.8,
    "nitrogen": 120.5,
    "phosphorus": 45.2,
    "potassium": 200.1
  }'
```

### Prochaines √©tapes

- Impl√©mentation des autres modules de pr√©diction
- Ajout de tests unitaires et d'int√©gration
- Am√©lioration des mod√®les de pr√©diction
- Ajout de fonctionnalit√©s d'authentification et d'autorisation

Thanks for your contribution!
Please read this comment in its entirety. It's quite important.

# Pull Request title

It should be in the following format:

```
gh-NNNNNN: Summary of the changes made
```

Where: gh-NNNNNN refers to the GitHub issue number.

Most PRs will require an issue number. Trivial changes, like fixing a typo, do not need an issue.

# Backport Pull Request title

If this is a backport PR (PR made against branches other than `main`),
please ensure that the PR title is in the following format:

```
[X.Y] <title from the original PR> (GH-NNNNNN)
```

Where: [X.Y] is the branch name, for example: [3.13].

GH-NNNNNN refers to the PR number from `main`.

-->

issue.title: Add Print & Export PDF feature for FoodDetail page
issue.body:
## üìå Pull Request Summary

- Added Print & Export as PDF functionality to the FoodDetail page.
- Print: Uses react-to-print (v3 API) to open the browser print dialog with a clean recipe layout.
- Export PDF: Uses html2pdf.js to download the food/recipe details as a styled PDF file.
- Added print.css to hide non-essential UI (buttons, Add to Cart) and improve print/PDF layout.
- Buttons styled to match the Add to Cart color theme.
- Added a print/PDF header with app branding and export date.


## üõ†Ô∏è Type of Change

Please select options that are relevant to your pull request

- [ ] üêõ Bug fix  
- [x] ‚ú® New feature  
- [ ] üßπ Code refactor  
- [ ] üß™ Tests added/updated  
- [ ] üìÑ Documentation update  
- [ ] üöÄ Performance improvement  
- [ ] üîß Other (please describe):

## üîó Related Issue

Closes #156 



## ‚úÖ Checklist

Please confirm the following before submitting:

- [x] I have **tested** my changes locally
- [x] I have run `npm run dev` or similar to check code style
- [x] I have updated documentation (if necessary)
- [x] My code follows the project‚Äôs coding conventions
- [x] I have merged the latest `main` or `dev` branch
- [x] I have performed a **self-review** of my own code.
- [x] My changes **generate** no new warnings or errors.
- [x] I have **commented** my code, especially in hard-to-understand areas
- [x] I have **linked the related issue**


---
## üß† Additional Notes

1) Tested on Chrome and Firefox; confirmed CORS-safe image loading in PDF.
2) Layout ensures no awkward page breaks for ingredients or steps.
3) Feature improves usability for offline users and those who prefer printed recipes.

pull_request.title: üé® B2B Frontend Transformation: Regional Browsing + Lot Creation + QR Pickup
pull_request.body:
## üé® B2B Marketplace Frontend Transformation

This PR completes the frontend transformation from collectibles auctions to a hyperlocal B2B surplus marketplace, implementing the core user workflows for business equipment, construction materials, and commercial goods.

### üöÄ **New Pages & Features**

**Homepage Transformation** (`Index.tsx`)
- ‚úÖ B2B-focused hero section with regional market emphasis
- ‚úÖ Business equipment categories (Construction, Restaurant, Office, Municipal)
- ‚úÖ "Find Lots Near You" with location-based browsing
- ‚úÖ Success stories from local businesses

**Regional Browsing** (`RegionPage.tsx`)
- ‚úÖ Distance-based filtering (5, 15, 30+ miles)
- ‚úÖ Hyperlocal lot discovery with PostGIS integration
- ‚úÖ Business verification tier badges (T0-T3)
- ‚úÖ Real-time location detection and region selection

**Lot Creation** (`CreateLotPage.tsx`)
- ‚úÖ Comprehensive B2B lot creation form
- ‚úÖ Business-specific fields (condition, dimensions, specifications)
- ‚úÖ Category selection for target verticals
- ‚úÖ Pickup location and timeframe settings
- ‚úÖ Reserve pricing and auction duration controls

**QR Scanner** (`QRScannerPage.tsx`)
- ‚úÖ Camera-based QR code scanning for pickup verification
- ‚úÖ Manual code entry fallback option
- ‚úÖ Integration with pickup confirmation Edge Function
- ‚úÖ Automatic seller payout trigger

**Updated Routing** (`App.tsx`)
- ‚úÖ `/r/:regionSlug` - Regional marketplace browsing
- ‚úÖ `/sell/new` - Create new B2B lot
- ‚úÖ `/pickup/:lotId/scan` - QR pickup verification
- ‚úÖ `/browse` - General browsing with location filters

### üèóÔ∏è **Key Transformations**

**From Collectibles ‚Üí B2B Surplus:**
- Auction timing: Live events ‚Üí Always-on soft-close auctions
- Inventory: TCG/LEGO ‚Üí Business equipment & materials  
- Audience: Collectors ‚Üí Local businesses & contractors
- Pickup: Event-based ‚Üí Scheduled local pickup only

**Hyperlocal Focus:**
- PostGIS distance calculations for bidding eligibility
- Regional market organization by metro areas
- Local pickup verification with QR codes
- Business verification tiers for trust & access

### üîÑ **Integration with Backend**

Works seamlessly with PR #1 (B2B Schema Foundation):
- New database schema for businesses, regions, locations
- Enhanced bidding with radius validation
- Stripe Connect for business seller onboarding
- QR-based pickup with automatic escrow release

### üì± **Mobile-First Design**

- Responsive layouts for all new pages
- Touch-friendly QR scanner interface
- Mobile-optimized lot browsing and creation
- Progressive Web App readiness

### üöÄ **Next Phase Ready**

This frontend transformation enables:
1. **AI Integration** - Listing assistance, pricing optimization
2. **Mobile Apps** - Native QR scanning and push notifications  
3. **Analytics** - Regional marketplace health dashboards
4. **Advanced Features** - Bulk lot management, bidding automation

---

**Ready for Testing** üß™  
All new routes functional with comprehensive error handling and loading states. Preserves existing functionality while introducing B2B-focused user flows.

**Implements Tasks #9-15** from the 25-task roadmap.

issue.title: Sketch: Error shows when 'endpoint' of a circle is selected when outside of sketch mode
issue.body:

### Problem description

Steps to reproduce:

- open file (remove the .zip extension)

[FC-sketch-circle.FCStd.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/21822951/FC-sketch-circle.FCStd.zip)

- select the 'endpoint' of the circle

https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e07f80b9-46bc-4421-9f1b-f0715c295d3c

I am able to reproduce in Safe Mode.

The MRT Note Importer has been greatly revamped and is now the Raid Setup Importer, that allows to import in one shot:
- MRT Notes
- MRT Raid group
- Stormlash rotation
- Banner rotation

Wiki can be found here

Merge pull request #727 from pkimetal/auto-dev-update

Dependency Update

Merge pull request #728 from pkimetal/auto-dev-update

Dependency Update

Update social media configuration and logging enhancements

- Clarified the purpose of `SOCIAL_POST_MAX_COUNT` in the configuration file.
- Introduced a new document, `TWITTER_FETCH_ISSUE_FINDINGS.md`, detailing issues and resolutions related to Twitter fetching.
- Updated the admin controller to use a configurable limit for social posts retrieval.
- Enhanced the scoring service to utilize the configurable limit for LLM assessment, improving flexibility in post handling.
